I get a tell from *some guy* of *some uber guild*. OK...I get my grp port in and he says he can't pay me. I tell him no big deal. was just heading in that direction anyway, not porting for cash. <br>
<br>
We get to WC, I SoW him, and he hands me a gold earring. I take it..why not? I just spent a bunch of money on spells and every cp helps. Thanks, disband, and run to EC. Halfway on my run through EC i see an auction by..you guessed who..*some guy*...&quot;WTB whatever quest gem it was&quot;...So I'm thinking &quot;??!!??!?!&quot;.<br>
<br>
All I can say is &quot;Dude! I never asked for anything. Why bother with the pretense??&quot;<br>
<br>
And before someone gets on my butt about it being for the money...no. I don't care about that. But why the fuck play mind games when you so obviously don't have to??<br>
<br>
<br>
*note: took out the name of the person and guild since i'm sure a bazillion ppl will be responding to my post about how he's such a great guy and the guild is the best and I'm just a greedy bitch who doesnt know any better...but as far as &quot;one person is not a whole guild&quot;, all I can say is MY estimition of this guild as gone down for just having such a person, which in turn makes me wonder how many others he has effected negetively in regards to that guilds rep.<br>
